What People Are Saying clipperadmin 2018-10-16T10:47:27-05:00 What People Are Saying “Hello I just wanted to follow up with you. We went in on Saturday for Angelina’s 13TH birthday party. It was such a great day from beginning to end. The staff is top notch, our waitress was so awesome, the food was delicious and the kids had a blast! Thank you so making my daughters day so special.” “I just got back from The Silverball Museum in Asbury Park New Jersey. All I can say is WOW! I was there once before but only for an hour. Today I was there for 4 hours. The admission prices are $10 for 1 hour $20 for all day or what I payed $15 for 10a.m. to 5 p.m. I also payed $1 an hour to park on the street, so I payed $5 just to be safe. Asbury Park may not look like much in some places, but the museum is WOW! All the machines (about 180 including pitch and bat but not video or skee ball) were fully functioning minus a few bulbs burnt out and WOZ being almost fully burnt out (the operator was working on it when I arrived and it was playable toward the end of the morning). All games are set to free play, have a description about the above the backbox and have high scores above the backbox for men, women and kids. The games I played the most were night rider, Evil Knievel, Genie and Medusa. There were too many em’s to mention as well. For $15 I was in heaven. Night Rider was the only game I came close to getting high score on which was about 101,000 and I got about 89,000. I highly recommend the place and the people are super friendly there. It was really great to play all the late Midway andWilliams tables. The only Stern ones were Elvis, TSPPP and Sopranos. Another really fun game was Pistol Poker by Alvin G. They also had a giant Pitch and bat machine that I liked. I could go on and on but that is enough for now. Put this place on your bucket list.” Source: https://www.vpforums.org/index.php?showtopic=24971 fusion-row #main © Copyright 2025 Silverball Museum.
